article.headline: Phillips has double-double in Bulldogs' victory
article.linkText: Defense, rebounding lift No. 16 Georgia in rout
article.story:
ATHENS, Ga. -- Porsha Phillips had 13 points and 13 rebounds to help Georgia (No. 16 ESPN/USA Today, No. 13 AP) beat Alabama-Birmingham 71-42 on Tuesday night.

Anne Marie Armstrong had 11 points and Meredith Mitchell finished with 10 for the Lady Bulldogs (7-0), who never trailed. Angel Robinson had 10 points and nine rebounds in her first game back since suffering a concussion against Rutgers on Nov. 22.

Tamika Dukes scored 12 points for UAB (2-5), and Amber Jones had nine.

Georgia outrebounded the Blazers 49-31. UAB shot 26 percent (15 for 57) from the field.
